sns.set(style="white")

# Compute the correlation matrix
corr = X_train_8.corr()

# Generate a mask for the upper triangle
mask = np.zeros_like(corr, dtype=np.bool)
mask[np.triu_indices_from(mask)] = True

# Set up the matplotlib figure
f, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(11, 9))

# Generate a custom diverging colormap
cmap = sns.diverging_palette(220, 10, as_cmap=True)

# Draw the heatmap with the mask and correct aspect ratio
sns.heatmap(corr, mask=mask, cmap=cmap, vmax=1, center=0,
            square=True, linewidths=.5, cbar_kws={"shrink": .5})

Step 3: Capping and transformation¶

In [31]:
# Cap sqft_living at 8,000 and sqft_lot at 800,000
df['sqft_living']= np.where(df['sqft_living'] >8000, 8000, df['sqft_living'])
df['sqft_lot']= np.where(df['sqft_lot'] >800000, 800000, df['sqft_lot'])
In [32]:
# Some properties have 0 bedrooms but it's clearly an error. To account for that, set 
# bedrooms=# of floors-1 if bedrooms=0
df['bedrooms']= np.where(df['bedrooms'] <1 , df['floors']-1, df['bedrooms'])
In [33]:
# Some properties have 0 bathrooms but it's clearly an error. To account for that, set 
# bathrooms=# of floors if bathrooms=0
df['bathrooms']= np.where(df['bathrooms'] <1, df['floors'], df['bathrooms'])
